Twenty-two-time grand slam champion Rafael Nadal gave a positive update about his fitness as he prepares to play at Wimbledon for the first time since 2019. The 36-year-old Spaniard, entering London halfway to a calendar-year Grand Slam for the first time in his career, was on crutches after the French Open because of his chronic foot problem. But nerve treatment appears to have been successful. (With input from AP)